##Consensus and authority's opinion - a lazy way of defending our beliefs?

Despite all that, some people defend their own beliefs by trying to get a **consensus**, i.e., a majority of opinions similar to their own or by supporting them on an **authority's opinion**. However, many people having the same opinion or an 'authority' or 'expert' stating something, doesn't make it necessarily true - they're stating their *opinion* based not only on their knowledge but also on their personal insights on it <sup>([4][4])</sup>.

